The paper discusses the design choices for visualization thumbnails in online news articles, which involves aspects of human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The use of visualization in thumbnails also relates to multimedia (cs.MM) and graphics (cs.GR) research. Additionally, the paper mentions conversations with data journalists and news graphics designers, indicating a potential connection to natural language processing (cs.CL) in terms of understanding their perspectives and practices.
